<glossary>
<definition id="fs-idm351794944">
<term>business plan</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm343581072">formal document that typically describes the business and industry, market strategies, sales potential, and competitive analysis, as well as the company’s long-term goals and objectives</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm342554640">
<term>executive summary</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm601193472">initial section of a business plan document that summarizes the key elements of the entire plan</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm354389376">
<term>SWOT analysis</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm325689152">strategic analytical tool used to help a potential venture or existing company identify its strengths, weaknesses, opportunities, and threats related to business competition</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm357678448">
<term>competitive matrix</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm346890416">shows how and why a startup has a clear if not measurable competitive advantage for relevant features/benefits by weight according to customers, such as price and quality in relation to competitors</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
